# Pattern matching for null, type, and shape

Use C# patterns (`is null`, `is not null`, `is { … }`, `is Foo foo`) instead of `== null`, `!= null`, `as` + null check, or chained property guards.

## Preferred

```csharp
if (value is null) throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(value));
if (value is not null) Use(value);

if (request is { Tenant: { IsActive: true } tenant, Subject: not null }) Apply(tenant);

if (message is JsonObject obj) Process(obj);
```

## Avoid

```csharp
// Avoid
if (value == null) throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(value));
if (value != null) Use(value);

JsonObject obj = message as JsonObject;
if (obj != null) Process(obj);
```

## Scope

- Use `is null` / `is not null` for **all** null checks on reference types and `Nullable<T>`.
- Use property patterns `{ … }` to combine null + shape checks in one expression.
- Use type patterns `is T t` instead of `as` + null check.
- Pattern matching pairs naturally with the same-line guard rule (**`CSharp-Terse-01-GuardClausesSameLine.mdc`**).
